Based on the search results, here are the key findings about OpenSearch agentic query DSL type for executing agents:

## Query Structure

The agentic query allows you to ask questions in natural language and have OpenSearch automatically plan and execute the retrieval, working in conjunction with a preconfigured agent that reads the question, plans the search, and returns relevant results.

## Basic Search Request Body Example

A basic agentic search request looks like:

```
GET /_search?search_pipeline=agentic-pipeline
{
  "query": {
    "agentic": {
      "query_text": "Find me white shoes under 150 dollars"
    }
  }
}
```


## Search Pipeline Configuration

To set up the search pipeline, you configure an agentic_query_translator processor with the agent_id:

```
PUT /_search/pipeline/agentic_search_pipeline
{
  "request_processors": [
    {
      "agentic_query_translator": {
        "agent_id": "your-agent-id-here"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```


## Query Execution Flow

The agentic search request executes the agent with the QueryPlanningTool and sends the natural language question, along with the index mapping and a default prompt, to an LLM to generate a DSL query.

## Optional Query Fields

You can optionally specify query fields that the agent should consider:

```
GET iris-index/_search?search_pipeline=agentic-pipeline
{
  "query": {
    "agentic": {
      "query_text": "List all the flowers present",
      "query_fields": ["species", "petal_length_in_cm"]
    }
  }
}
```


